"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَحْبِسُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَحْبِسْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَحْبِس","in_corpus":true,"count":20,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَحْبِس","in_corpus":true,"count":11,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَحْبِسانِ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَحْبِسا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَحْبِسانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَحْبِسا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَحْبِسُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَحْبِسُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَحْبِسْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"حَبَسْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"حَبَسْتُ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَحْبِس","in_corpus":true,"count":2,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَحْبِس","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"}],"frequency_in_corpus":69,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n6906","n6907","n6908"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to imprison"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hold back"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَبَسَ (ḥabasa) (form I); imprisonment, confinement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَبَسَ (ḥabasa) (form I); retention, holding back"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prison, jail","examples":[{"text":"فخرجت إلى الساحل أربد بكلة وهذا أول الهند ومنتهى مسير المراكب لا يتهيّأ لها أن يتجاوزها وألا غرقت قال فلما وصلت إلى كلة رأيته وهي عظيمة عالية السور كثيرة البساتين غزيرة الماء ووجدت بها معدن الرصاص القلعي لا يكون إلا في قلعتها في سائر الدنيا، وفي هذه القلعة تضرب السيوف القلعية، وهي الهندية العتيقة … وأهل هذه القلعة يمتنعون على ملكها إذا أرادوا يطيعونه إن أحبوا ورسمهم رسم الصين في ترك الذبائح وليس في جميع الدنيا معدن الرصاص القلعي إلا في هذه القلعة وبينهما وبين الصين ثلثمائة فرسخ وحولها مدن ورساتيق وقرى ولهم أحكام وحبوس وخبايات وأكلهم البر والتمور وبقولهم كلها تباع وزنا وأرغفة خبزهم تباع عددا ولا حمامات لهم بل عندهم عين جارية يغتسلون فيها ودرهمهم يزن ثلثي درهم ويعرف بالفهري ولهم فلوس يتعاملون بها ويلبسون كأهل الصين الإفرند الصيني المثمن وملكها دون ملك الصين ويخطب لملك الصين وقبلته إليه وبيت عبادته له.","english":"And I went off to the dusty shore of Kala, which is the first and ultimate end of India for vessels, as nobody even dares to imagine to pass by it since he would drown. When I arrived at Kala, I conned it and it is large and has high walls, many gardens and plenty of water, and I found mines of tin not found in the rest of the world but in Qalʿa, and in this Qalʿa one forges the Qalʿaite swords, the excellent Indian ones, and the populace of this Qalʿa withstands its king when it wants and abides by him when it lists, and their tradition is like the tradition of China, refraining from slaughtering beasts, and there aren’t in all the world tin mines but in this Qalʿa, and between them two and China are three-hundred parasang, and there are towns, rural districts and villages, and they have jurisdiction, jails, and corbans, and their food is wheat and dates and all their vegetables they buy by scales, and their bread is bread-rolls they buy by count. They have no baths but a running spring in which they wash, and their dirham weighs as a third-dirham and is known as Fahrī, and they have fulūs with which they commerce, and they dress like the people of China in dear Chinese silks, and their king is subordinate to the King of China, reports to the King of China, his praying direction is to him, his place of sacrifice is towards him."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tie up","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a form of property on real estate that binds it to a religious administration and assigns its earnings to charitable purposes, waqf, mortmain"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew חָבַשׁ (ḥāḇaš, “to bind, tie”).\n\nCompare Egyptian ḥbs, Hebrew חָבַשׁ (khavásh)."},"ipa":["/ħab.ba.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6906","headword_ar":"حَبْسٌ","root":"Hbs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of confinement, restriction, imprisonment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like; a prison; a jail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHobasN","text_ar":"مَحْبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, A, TA,) which is also an inf. n.; (Lth, TA;) or, accord. to analogy, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHobisN","text_ar":"مَحْبِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb, TA:) pl. of the first,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwsN","text_ar":"حُبُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and of the second [and third],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAbisu","text_ar":"مَحَابِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibosN","text_ar":"حِبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Lth","A","TA","Sb"]},{"entry_id":"n6907","headword_ar":"حُبْسٌ","root":"Hbs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubusN","text_ar":"حُبُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiysN","text_ar":"حَبِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (IAth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6908","headword_ar":"حِبْسٌ","root":"Hbs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dam constructed of wood or stones, in a channel of water, to confine the water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that people may drink from it and water their beasts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabosN","text_ar":"حَبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (El-'Ámiree, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaAsN","text_ar":"اَحْبَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibaAsN","text_ar":"حِبَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Meyd, in Golius:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dam by which the water-course of a valley is obstructed, in any place where it is confined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones put in the mouth of a river"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rivulet"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, preventing the overflowing of the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSonaEap","text_ar":"مَصْنَعَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawoD","text_ar":"حَوْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-ing-trough for beasts"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the rain-water is collected;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAbisN","text_ar":"حَابِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSonaEap","text_ar":"مَصْنَعَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K:) pl."},{"kind":"page_break","n":501},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaAsN","text_ar":"اَحْبَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AA, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubaAsapN","text_ar":"حُبَاسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibaAsapN","text_ar":"حِبَاسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibosN","text_ar":"حِبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to Lth, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HbAsAt","text_ar":"حباسات"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a piece of land are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what surround a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of ground such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daborapN","text_ar":"دَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is the same as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aArap","text_ar":"مَشَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the water is confined until they are full, when it is made to flow to other parts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hibos","text_ar":"حِبْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is surrounded by dams"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by ridges of earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which confine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retain, the water"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for irrigation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aArapN","text_ar":"مَشَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daborapN","text_ar":"دَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (R, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wr","text_ar":"شور"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water collected, and having no supply to increase it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K:) thus called by the name of that by which it is confined. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","IAar","AA"]}]}}